LUXEMBOURG (AP) _ Atento SA (ATTO) on Wednesday reported a loss of $43.7 million in its fourth quarter.The Luxembourg-based company said it had a loss of $3.11 per share. Losses, adjusted for non-recurring costs, came to $2.43 per share.The customer relationship management and business process outsourcing services company posted revenue of $327.2 million in the period.For the year, the company reported that its loss widened to $90.3 million, or $6.42 per share. Revenue was reported as $1.45 billion.Atento shares have climbed 19% since the beginning of the year. The stock has risen 47% in the last 12 months._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on ATTO at https://www.zacks.com/ap/ATTO